				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="レッツ・プレイ・イノベーション！！ (Let&#039;s Play Innovation!!)" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#172;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#131;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#132;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#187;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#151;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#172;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#164;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#187;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#164;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#142;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#153;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#188;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#183;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#167;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#179;&amp;#239;&amp;#188;&amp;#129;&amp;#239;&amp;#188;&amp;#129; (Let's Play Innovation!!) is a Japanese card game developed by a company specialising in business training. The core idea of the game is that players must go through a number of business failures before reaching success. That is, you cannot win the game without first failing. The process is intended to teach resilience, innovation, and the benefits of trial and error.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;During the game, the players operate a business and aim for success. The game has a deck of cards, each providing different events, some progress their goals, some set them back, some provide new opportunities. Players try to develop their enterprise and turn setbacks into innovations, with a take that element in gameplay.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players draw to their hand and then play from their hand. Some cards have special enhancing effects to already played cards. Most of the cards are split diagonally, with a positive side, and a black negative side. When a player puts the card into their tableau, they can turn it to show the positive benefits, or turn it to show the negative failures. Players must build on their failures before they can win.&amp;#10;user summary&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
